cc.name: configuration controlled 3D design of mechanical parts and assemblies with additions
cc.description: This is the only conformance class defined for this part of ISO 10303. It can be combined with any of the conformance options listed below.

co.name: Activity
co.description: The conformance option Activity provides the capability to a define typical and individual activities with properties and to relate them to other objects.

co.name: Advanced boundary representation
co.description: The conformance option Advanced boundary representation provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by three dimensional topologically bounded solids with elementary and free form surfaces and edges.

co.name: Alias identification
co.description: The conformance option Alias identification provides the capability to add additional alias IDs to Parts and other objects in addition to the default one of these objects.

co.name: Alternate product and assembly component substitution
co.description: The conformance option Alternate product and assembly component substitution provides the capability to define products as potential replacements for other products and the substitution of components in an assembly by components of other types.

co.name: Approval
co.description: The conformance option Approval provides the capability to represent planned and actual approvals.

co.name: Assembly with shape
co.description: The conformance option Contextual shape positioning provides the capability for the representation of assemblies with geometric transformation data of the components.

co.name: Assembly with usage dependent shape of components
co.description: The conformance option Contextual shape positioning provides the capability for the representation of assemblies with components of flexible material whose shape depend on the usage within the assembly. Example1: The shape of parts made out of rubber often differs when used as components in an assembly from the original shape. Example2: The shape of a flexible cable or tube within an assembly.

co.name: Associative draughting
co.description: The conformance option Associative draughting provides the capability to to associate annotation elements that presents dimensions or draughting callouts of a draughting model with elements of the shape of a product.

co.name: Basic assembly
co.description: The conformance option Basic assembly provides the capability to define simple assembly structures without re-use of assembly components for different variants or versions and without effectivity and configuration control of the used parts and components.

co.name: Basic callout without associativity
co.description: The conformance option Basic callout without associativity provides the capability to define callouts, consisting of text or symbols, leader, direction or projection curve and terminator symbols.

co.name: Basic classification
co.description: The conformance option Basic classification provides the capability to define classes and to relate elements of product data to these classes.

co.name: Basic document
co.description: The conformance option Basic document provides the capability to identify documents, versions and different views of a documents and to relate them to external files and and to product data.

co.name: Basic product property
co.description: The conformance option Basic product property provides the capability to represent simple properties of products, consisting of the property type, property value and the underlying unit.

co.name: Basic text and curve presentation
co.description: The conformance option Basic text and curve presentation provides the capability to represent text together with styling information for pre-defined or externally defined fonts.

co.name: Certification
co.description: The conformance option Certification provides the capability to assign certifications to product data.

co.name: Colours and layers
co.description: The conformance option Colours and layers provides the capability to group presentation elements, define layers and assign colours.

co.name: Complex product property
co.description: The conformance option Complex product property provides the capability to share and exchange properties which may be base properties, which may be qualified or have some specified uncertainty, or a property which may be an aggregate of other properties.

co.name: Composite materials
co.description: The conformance option Composite materials provides the capability to identify materials and to represent the chemical composition, material properties and surface characteristics of products.

co.name: Compound shape representation
co.description: The conformance option Compound shape representation provides the capability to

co.name: Constructive solid geometry 3d
co.description: The conformance option Constructive solid geometry 3d provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by Constructive Solid Geometry (CSG) conveyed by solid models, and the structural information is communicated through acyclic graphs.

co.name: Construction geometry
co.description: The conformance option Construction geometry provides the capability to

co.name: Contract and project
co.description: The conformance option Contract and project provides the capability to represent contract and project information.

co.name: Curve swept solid
co.description: The conformance option Curve swept solid provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by a three dimensional solids with a fixed cross-section along a centre curve with orientation. The cross-section may be either circular or any other form. The intended usage is to represent the shape of cables or tubes.

co.name: Date and time
co.description: The conformance option Date and time provides the capability to assign a date or a date with time to some other objects in user defined or predefined roles.

co.name: Document structure and properties
co.description: The conformance option Document structure and properties provides the capability to describe hierarchies of documents, classes of document and properties of document.

co.name: Edge based wireframe
co.description: The conformance option Edge based wireframe provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by a three-dimensional wireframe model whose curves are topologically bounded.

co.name: Effectivity
co.description: The conformance option Effectivity provides the capability to define the effectivity of items according to the date, time interval, lot or serial number.

co.name: Elementary boundary representation
co.description: The conformance option Elementary boundary representation provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by three dimensional topologically bounded solids with elementary surfaces and edges.

co.name: Enhanced assembly
co.description: The conformance option Enhanced assembly provides the capability to define complex assembly and collection structures including reuse of the same assembly components for assemblies of different variants and versions.

co.name: Event and time interval
co.description: The conformance option Event and time interval provides the capability to

co.name: Extended classification
co.description: The conformance option Extended classification provides the capability to define classification systems with attributes and to refer to part library classification services.

co.name: External library
co.description: The conformance option External library provides the capability to link product data with externally defined library and dictionary services.

co.name: External model
co.description: The conformance option External model provides the capability to to link external geometry models that may be based on standard or proprietary formats with parts and other kinds of products.

co.name: Faceted boundary representation
co.description: The conformance option Faceted boundary representation provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by three dimensional topologically bounded solids with planar surfaces with explicit edge-curves.

co.name: Geometric placement within physical breakdown elements
co.description: The conformance option Geometric placement provides the capability to to place the occurrence of a part or a physical breakdown element with another physical breakdown element.

co.name: Information rights
co.description: The conformance option Information rights provides the capability to represent rights concerning the access and use of information.

co.name: GD&T presentation
co.description: The conformance option GD&T presentation provides the capability for the presentation of Geometric Dimensioning and Tolerancing information of the shape of a product.

co.name: GD&T presentation with association
co.description: The conformance option GD&T presentation with association provides the capability for the associated presentation and representation of Geometric Dimensioning and Tolerancing information of the shape of a product.

co.name: GD&T representation
co.description: The conformance option GD&T representation provides the capability for the representation of Geometric Dimensioning and Tolerancing information of the shape of a product.

co.name: Geometrically bounded surface
co.description: The conformance option Geometrically bounded surface provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by three-dimensional surfaces that are geometrically bounded.

co.name: Geometrically bounded wireframe
co.description: The conformance option Geometrically bounded wireframe provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by three-dimensional wireframe models whose curves are geometrically bounded.

co.name: Manifold subsurface
co.description: The conformance option Manifold subsurface provides the capability to

co.name: Manifold surface
co.description: The conformance option Manifold surface provides the capability to

co.name: Materials
co.description: The conformance option Materials provides the capability to identify materials and to represent the chemical composition, material properties and surface characteristics of products.

co.name: Mechanical design geometric presentation
co.description: The conformance option Mechanical design geometric presentation provides the capability for the representation of the visual presentation of the shape of mechanical design models.

co.name: Mechanical design presentation representation with draughting
co.description: The conformance option Mechanical design presentation representation with draughting provides the capability for the representation of a styled model for mechanical design presentation which is composed of draughting models and other mechanical design style models.

co.name: Mechanical design shaded presentation
co.description: The conformance option Mechanical design shaded presentation provides the capability for the representation of advanced visual presentations of the shape of mechanical design models.

co.name: Modified swept solid
co.description: The conformance option Modified swept solid provides the capability to

co.name: Multi linguism
co.description: The conformance option Multi linguism provides the capability to represent names and description of objects in different languages. In addition alternative names can be provided.

co.name: Non manifold surface
co.description: The conformance option Non manifold surface provides the capability to

co.name: Part make from relationship
co.description: The conformance option Part make from relationship provides the capability to

co.name: Partial document and structured text representation
co.description: The conformance option Partial document and structured text representation provides the capability to represent structured tagged text as content of a document and to refer to portions of this text.

description.p: The conformance option Person and organization provides the capability to define persons, organization and addresses and to relate the combination of those to Parts and other objects in a particular role.
Example: The person "Fred Flintstone" who is an employee from the organization "Stone Times Inc." is the "creator" of version "v1" of the part "Stone Vehicle One".

co.name: Physical and functional breakdown
co.description: The conformance option Physical and functional breakdown provides the capability for the partitioning of a product into a set of related functional and physical elements.

co.name: Planned and evaluated characteristics
co.description: The conformance option Planned and evaluated characteristics provides the capability to

co.name: Product class and specification
co.description: The conformance option Product class and specification provides the capability for the representation of the identification and characterization of families of similar products to be offered to the market and to identify particular member of the family of products with selected characteristics.

co.name: Product concept
co.description: The conformance option Product concept provides the capability for the representation of the identification of a product or a family products proposed to customers.

co.name: Product configuration
co.description: The conformance option Product configuration provides the capability to represent design information that is related with selected characteristic elements and their conditional combination of family of products offered to market.

co.name: Product version relationship
co.description: The conformance option Product version relationship provides the capability to define sequences, hierarchies and derivations between versions of the same or different products and to record the fact that two versions of different products are intended to be the same.

co.name: Production rule
co.description: The conformance option Production rule provides the capability for the representation of the information needed to describe design constraints, commonly referred to as rules.

co.name: Requirement
co.description: The conformance option Requirement provides the capability to

co.name: Saved view
co.description: The conformance option Saved view provides the capability to store camera positions of three dimensional styles models together with selected appearance styles and annotations.

co.name: Security classification
co.description: The conformance option Security classification provides the capability to

co.name: Shape feature
co.description: The conformance option Shape feature provides the capability for the representation of a shape oriented shape_feature, either defined in place or alternately by placing a referenced shape_feature.

co.name: Shape validation property
co.description: The conformance option Shape validation property provides the capability for the representation of shape validation properties, including centre point, volume, surface and moment of inertia.

co.name: Shell based wireframe
co.description: The conformance option Shell based wireframe provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by three-dimensional wireframe models whose curves are bounded by a set of shells.

co.name: Software
co.description: The conformance option Software provides the capability to represent software as a product with versions and to identify the sources, object and other files for this software.

co.name: Solid with local modification
co.description: The conformance option Solid with local modification provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by a three dimensional modified solid with local changes. The types of modification permitted include edge based modifications, face based modifications and the introduction of depressions, protrusions of different shapes and regular patterns of these features.

co.name: Solid with construction history
co.description: The conformance option Solid with construction history provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by a three dimensional solid that is created by procedural modifications of another solid.

co.name: Solutions for physical and functional breakdown
co.description: The conformance option Solutions for physical and functional breakdown provides the capability to to represent occurrences of parts as realized solutions for a functional or organic requirement and also to provide alternative solutions.

co.name: Specification control
co.description: The conformance option Specification control provides the capability for the representation of products with a large number of variants.

co.name: Swept solid
co.description: The conformance option Swept solid provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by three dimensional solids that are created by sweeping a face.

co.name: Technical drawing
co.description: The conformance option Technical drawing provides the capability to exchange two dimensional technical drawings with multiple pages.

co.name: Technical drawing with pictures
co.description: The conformance option Technical drawing with pictures provides the capability to exchange two dimensional technical drawings with multiple pages that can include pictures.

co.name: Text with specified font
co.description: The conformance option Text with specified font provides the capability to represent text together with detailed stroke and outline font.

co.name: Thickened face solid
co.description: The conformance option Thickened face solid provides the capability to represent the shape of a product by a three dimensional solid created by thickening a face. The face is topologically bounded and has fully defined geometry. The material added may be on one, or both, sides of the original face.

co.name: Work organization
co.description: The conformance option Work organization provides the capability to represent a work request to perform particular kinds of activities for an identified set of items and to represent a work order by which the work request is authorized to be addressed.
